        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 2:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
capable of producing a landspout near Queens Reservoir, or 15 miles
north of Lamar, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 40 mph, and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hartman and Queens Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
